The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Electrosteel Castings Ltd (ECL) has reported an 18.5 per cent increase in turnover at Rs 1,331 crore for the 2007-08 fiscal against Rs 1,123 crore in the previous year. Profits before tax declined 30 per cent to Rs.110.65 crore from Rs 158.42 crore a year ago. For the quarter ended March 31, 2008, the company recorded a turnover of Rs 415.29 crore compared with Rs 311.11 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal.                             
	 Geojit Financial Services has entered into a pact with UTI Mutual Fund to provide its employees a retirement planning opportunity through UTI Retirement Benefit Pension Fund.                             
	 Shyam Steel Industries Ltd has announced a Rs 100-crore expansion project for its Durgapur plant, which produces 0.4 tonnes of TMT bars annually.                             
	 Zodiac has launched the linen collection for summer 2008 called Positano. The collection comprising striped designs is priced at Rs 1,699.                            
